HEADWORD: Trigone
<hw>Tri`gone"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., literally,
a trigon.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A smooth triangular area on the
inner surface of the bladder, limited by the apertures of the ureters
and urethra.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

